Package utils

Class ObjectsList

java.lang.Object
utils.ObjectsList
public class ObjectsList extends Object
This class is used to create differents arrays of objects. Its a poor and limited copy of the Arrays.list that I make during my classes to learn how to manage objects.

The class have methods to add and delete objects from the list, merge lists, search for objects or index and others.

Author:
Fernando Tarrino del Pozo (FernandoEsra)

    • addOnIndex

      public void addOnIndex(Object toAdd, int index)
      Create a new array with one more length that are a copy of the actual array. Then using System.arraycopy() copy all from the index but one position ahead. Finally add the new item tho the indicated index.
      Parameters:
      toAdd - A object to add to the list.
      index - Where to add the new object.

    • mergeLists

      public void mergeLists(ObjectsList otherObjectList)
      Create a new array wich is a copy of the actual array but with length equal to the length of the actual array and the array in the otherObjectList. Then copy all the Objects of the otherObjectList starting from final index of the original list.

      Important: This method change the actual list, does not return anything.

      Parameters:
      otherObjectList - A ObjectsList object.

    • eraseFromIndex

      public void eraseFromIndex(int index)
      Search if the index provided exists, if exists, delete the character by overwrite all the index, starting in the provied index, from the object that are one position ahead. Then create a copy of the array with one less length.
      Parameters:
      index - A index to delete one object.

    • getObjectOnIndex

      public Object getObjectOnIndex(int index)
      Search on the array if the index exists, if exists return the object inside the index.
      Parameters:

      Returns:
